extendedInfo.description: Create and play back guitar tabs.  Up to 15 simultaneous tracks, including multiple drum tracks.Supported features:*Two input modes*128 instruments*Independent string tuning*Volume swells*Independent string volumes*Bend swells*Tempo changes*Instrument changes*Customizable hotkeys for most functions*Play selection*Export midi*Export txt*much more!

reviews.title: Could be great.
reviews.comment: Bit buggy,  crashes somewhat often.  Would love the ability to play a section in a loop.  Good for getting stuff down quick,  probably worth the money but still needs some work.
reviews.author: Steven k

reviews.title: Great App
reviews.comment: This app does exactly what i need it to do. It is a great little tool for sitting down and working out new songs or if you are out and get an idea running through your head. The developer offers great customer support. As this is the only app on the market that does what i need it too I was slightly disappointed when a few crashes happened. After emailing the developer with my concerns he promptly responded and my problems were fixed within 24 hours. Thank you for this great tool.
reviews.author: Randy Miller

reviews.title: Great app
reviews.comment: Just what i was lookin for...
reviews.author: Issac Sanchez

reviews.title: The best, but only because it\'s the only one.
reviews.comment: I\'ve been searching for an app that would let me write tabs on the go so I downloaded pretty much all the other so-called \"tabs\" apps. Every single one was only to access a database to download other band\'s tabs... nothing useful for those who actually like to CREATE. Pros: +multitrack +playback +only app to create. Cons: -hard to learn (you can have more than 6 measures per songs, good luck finding how) -buggy -no triplets/grouping -no actual note duration selection
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: There are three
reviews.comment: Guitar Partner, Guitar Pro and this. This one is the best for multi track on a touchscreen. Guitar Pro does not do multitrack but has a nice interface. Guitar Partner crashes and is not designed well for a touchscreen only phone
